    "description": "The strategy exploits the well documented turn of month equity return seasonality by taking systematic long exposure to US large cap equities around month end and early month. It trades a single liquid instrument, SPY (S&amp;P 500 ETF), seeking to capture the tendency for positive flows and stronger returns from the last trading day of a month through the first few trading days of the next month.\n\nExecution is fully rules based and calendar scheduled using the official US trading calendar: it en",
    "description_full": "The strategy exploits the well documented turn of month equity return seasonality by taking systematic long exposure to US large cap equities around month end and early month. It trades a single liquid instrument, SPY (S&amp;P 500 ETF), seeking to capture the tendency for positive flows and stronger returns from the last trading day of a month through the first few trading days of the next month.\n\nExecution is fully rules based and calendar scheduled using the official US trading calendar: it enters by buying SPY at the market open on the last trading day of each month (submitted shortly before the open) and exits by liquidating the entire position at the market close on the third trading day of the new month. Position sizing is constant at 100 percent notional long when active and 0 percent otherwise, with no leverage, no stop loss, and no explicit volatility or drawdown targeting. Decisions are made at daily frequency based solely on date and time rules rather than price signals, implying the primary risk is broad equity market beta concentrated in the turn of month holding window.",
